      "content": "Taking oxycodone for a headache is an unnecessary risk because opioids can cause dangerous respiratory depression, especially if you have any undiagnosed sleep apnea or lung issues. Furthermore, opioids interact with acetaminophen to increase the risk of liver damage, and they carry a high potential for addiction and severe side effects like constipation or sedation. You should strictly stick to the acetaminophen you have on hand and avoid mixing it with any other medications unless explicitly instructed by a pharmacist or doctor.",
